spanGrp.span: Well I will tell a story about a king
Anal jol akheh linu pakan jol akheh linu
He married a girl of Anal tribe, a Pakan lady
vatum hno nathung chamang jol linu
after that he married a witch,
The first lady he married was Anal
chamang nutuwng datung patho ningsung amaheeng
the lady witch was thinking how to kill her
kapamang do hrang vamo kapatho do hrang vamo vado tol va
how to get rid of her? how to kill her? she thought
And, the witch told to her husband
she always try to find out her mistakes .
pakan jolheeng Anal jol heeng damo chaka apatho dovah vadonate
"let's ehm... hey, kill the Anal woman!", she told (the king)
sinnu tuwng donu lupanu tuwng vasinnu rowlsa kituwng donu
hal ihrung hrang kapahring chakhin o ah vado nate
She said "Let me live so I could look after the chickens"
tuso donibe dahtung dochaka vakhu patho chakamo
(the king and the witch) so what should we do? Let's break her leg
vahmi akheh akhal pehloh chakave dojenu vahmi akheh to akhal hloh jenu
Let's take out her eye, they said, and did so.
and they let her look after the chicken
and the wife that he married before
ing Anal nu vanalo chapa akheh vathovah
yes, the Anal lady had a son
(the witch) let me send this boy away and
damo kanu kapa hintuwng acha doh vahso vadonate
let my parent and family eat him away, she said
le jungso chaka kanu kapa hin kuwng ha jungpajoon vaso
let's send him to my parents and families
she said, our son - she said
vadonate nalanglangva donu vainpu tuwngte vathima vato
the king agreed but he did not know
ama e ama kachapa e vajungcha
as soon as my son arrives
akhal hinnu acha doh khin no vadova
stab him and eat him, she said
donu chethito toonu vathongja thung vathalpevah
the letter she wrote was put inside his pocket
the son didn't know his stepmother's plan and went
she put him on a white horse
as he kept and kept on riding
asinki vanute ate chatang to vapahrung javah
his mother was let look after grains
amato vajungjung vajungjung jadohnu sinpa charato
as he was riding, the boy
chakool lel vaungcha nate chakool te ikhung khung vato
as he was sitting on the horse, the horse got exhausted
ing damo kaning pootha kaning donu poo vathavah hlam thung tuwng ii-iiva
he decided to rest and slept on the road.
while he was sleeping, merchants came
ama sinpa chara i-iih hete dah vahol simo ato hin chaka dojenu
saying, "this sleeping boy, let us check what is his bag"
as they checked, the letter was found
which was written by his step mother
vapa najete ajungso donibe ama sinpa charahe
as they read it - "if the boy arrives
ahung palele makhin achadoh khin noh vadovah
don't let him return and eat him up", it says
damo tinkalal ulchahin tuwng ithajah pajo pejenu
the merchants wrote a good letter
ama sinpa charahe ajungso donibe an duduh bu duduh apekhin
saying,if the boy arrive give him a delicious meal
prepare a nice bed for him
and to take care of him properly
they wrote it in a letter for him
ahalpaki vanu napajote athujenu vapama doh vaje
What his mother wrote, they threw away and destroyed
nate vahangthi hlo nate aroh nihebe dingvaning atungbe
the boy woke up and asked himself "Oh What happened to me"
khujoong daldal ningnu donu tumkhe vajungchun vajung
it's about to be dark" and he rode off again
dah aholsih do- amahin tuwng te vapahrim dovaje
"What have you brought?" they welcomed him
vapahrim thung ihh... kauwnu vajungso varahmo vachala nutuwng
One aunt [thinks] "he must have been sent by my sister"
ing, chethito athu hlenu vapee najete
right, he took out a letter and hand it over to them
vapa nate ama sinpa chara ijunghe itha tangna sopa atopakhin
as they read, the boy who comes down - serve him properly
itha tangna ahlam hin nu athuwng pehinnu
feed him well, cook for him
prepare a nice bed for him
ing, chethi thung tuwng vapa nate
all that they read in the letter
icha dodo manu itha tangna vasuh vaje
so, instead of eating him, they took care of him
as they sat down, the mother first...
chamangnu chamangpa hinte velee choochaka vado thung jetuwng
the witch and the wizard/monster said "let's go there and back"
pirih vaje pirih choochaka vado thung jetuwng velee itung vaje
They used to stay overnight, as they said "let's stay overnight", they returned
"Let's go there and back" they said
atungki sinnu chara kuwngtuwng sinpa tuwng alaltuwng vapachool nate
Now a girl asked a boy about that.
kanuhin kapahin ne velee choohin chaka vado thung
"When my parents say - Let's go there and back"
pirih chochaka vadothung velee itung vaje
when they say "let's stay overnight", they come back
They stayed a day or two.
let us go and come back
nate anuhin apahin asinibe velee choohin chaka dojenu
so a boy says to a girl,''today your parents said they come back''
nate atungte pam ahol chakave vadonate
and [the boy said to the girl] "let us see your place"
inkhon to ahol chakave donu inkhon to vahol vaje
so they went to see the garden
tu thal te vain hinto kining kanang to vahrol valje
and they explored every corner of the house
amhete dahva dah athi vahin vadonate
and he asked "what do you keep here?"
kanuhin kapahin saru kanacha nahin kahre na vahin
[the girl] "these are bones that my parents and I eat and keep"
"Oho" he said. They went out. Then
as they went around, there was a river
amhete dah duva kangka duva donu
what is this river good for? - he asked
damo vahmiha patung sinbe vahmi lingka
if we put in into their eyes, they get cured"
thalki itho joso kangka du hlesinbe ajalka donu
and if we pour it onto a dead person, they will resurrect
amatuwng sinpa chara tuwng piruh tuwng duto suhtoonu
the boy secretly fetched some water
thongja thung vathal deeva atung mangnu
he ask again to a girl,what leaf is this?
ama thinghna he atahe apootoonu vavalki
this leaf, you randomly pluck it and throw...
how do you extinguish it? the boy asked
kadoka hla kadoka hla dohinnu kanam bubuh manghin donu
we murmur and murmur, and do it all like that
atuwl hete dah atuwlvah vadonate amhete
this grass - what is it? he said
amato asinki hmito apoonu piruh thongjathung vathal khuva
this is to stop a fire. He plucked it and also put into the bag
When our enemy is chasing us, we untie it
and it spreads as a rope
donu vathe pevah amato piruh tuwng apohnu vathalkhuvah
and again he secretly plucked it and put into his bag
they came back after walking around, and were tired
he thought to fight with him
they fought and fought and fought
vathal palahtuwng vaih najete setito atho samsamnu
both of them were lying and he saw bows hanging
ama te ama seti hete dakivah do(nu)
that, what are the bows like that?
"that one is my mother's tailbone, that one is my father's"
amhete kauhnu kowng amhete ni kakowng donu
That one is my sister's, that one is mine
ama tungbing hete daki apatho vahin donu
why these bottle gourds are hanging?
amate kapa luche kanu luche nika luche kauhnu luche donu
these are my father's head, my mother's head, my head and my sister's
he nagged and nagged and made the girl fall asleep
she fell asleep. As she fell asleep
petatang to hangkalnu asinki tungbing ru hruto
quitely he climbed up to the hanging things, a rope
the bows and the bottle gourd
vatohvaje pakunsamsam (jenu) amato apohnu vathongja thung thalnu
He got them, picked them and put into his bag
vanu vapahin asin velee choochaka vanado hinto hata kheh val icheeng doh vaje
the parents said we'll be back but left home for a week
vadonate pathiikaning no vadova katova vadonate
he said he is leaving and told [the girl] to follow him
ato namaningve kanuhin kapahin tungmale vano donu
she said "I will not follow you, my parents have no arrived yet"
vadonate chakol lel to tuwngnu vahung vahung vahung nate
vanuhin vapahinto ahmang thung tuwng vahmol hinto ipol- pun- pun tutuhvaje
her parents in the forest felt his back (?)
asinte vapo vaseto alal tuwng vahol po vanu vadonate
because the boy carried away all their things
atochaje amhete ding vame sopapammi dojenu
they got scared and wondered hat happened
vavangchun vavanjungje vavangchun into vasuh najete
they ran and ran and saw their home
there was only their daughter there
pavan to vahangsuna valuchehin vakownghin keh amma chave
when they look upward see nothing
they said "" and chased after him
arangte atho lulu te ijung vaje
In ancient times the could fly like wind
vadona vahungnun amheso amachin pangpang vadothung
he told it to scatter like fire and threw it
kado kahla kado kahla dojenu vanambuh valje
they murmured and did that all
then he threw the thorn grass
vadonate kado kahla kado kahla donu
asinki du- du akheh vanasuh hinto
just like that it flew as plenty of water
when they were about to reach
amahe ikanamave donu vapa luche vamakhuha vahemroh
he broke the head of the father (the bottle gourd) on his knee
then he broke the mother's head
vanu luche ruwng tungki nahla luche
his mother and a girl heads
then he carried his auntie's tailbone
chahkaning kauhnu natohe thami donu vanun
she chased because she did not like what her sister did
vaphadal dalthung valucheto vakowngto vapatho peval
when she tried to reach him he broke her head and tailbone
vakowngto thoocha dothal kite valucheto vahemval
her tailbone broke and then he cracked her head
hungtungcha vahung tungnate vanu dah vadi?
when he reached home, what does his [step]mother say?
aroh amahete jungnu, acha dokhin kadajalje
ah! as he went there, I told them to eat him
datona vahung patha vajecha donu nate
why did they send him away?
akhuchara hinso apakungvah apakungnu amato suhin chaka donu
and gather the people from your village. After that, let's see
nate kanuhe akolte va noh vado nate
mi chamang nuvah idote vathi mavato
people do not know she is a beast
vadona atung hate vakolte mito nungnungma thingnu
when the father held her tightly, many people arrived
seti to vakowngto ate vakho pimpim cheete
when he bent his stepmother's tailbone like that
vahmi parol ama didih vahmito parol thungthung parol thungthungnu
donate pa, pathama, pathama, akol akol akol donu
father, don't release her, keep hugging her
atungte amato tumkheh vakho pimpim vakho pimpimvah vakowngto
then he bent her tailbone again
vamhi parol dondon vahmol pasun sumsum donate
her eyes spark and her body hair grows up
apatho hrang va ti apatho va oh vadova
"if you are going to kill her - just kill her", he said
you took the [step]mother's suggestion, but my mother
vahmiche akhal hintinu hal pihrung hintinu
and you took out my mother's eyes and made her guard chickens
apatho hrang vahinning asaram chahin ithohrang vahinti vadonate
I have to kill both of you, you both must die
vapatuwng e ahh niso anu lulu o kahmi akheh kahal penu
but his father request him to spare his life like his mother
hal ihrung hrang kapahring chakhin o donu
let me live looking after poultry
asinki vanuto vakowng vakho peroh val
angu polcha valuche vahem peval thocha
she bent her head down, he broke it and she died
dona(te) vakhu chara hintuwng oho dojenu
donate vapato vahmicheto akhalpenu vakhu pathopenu
the he took out his father's eye and broke his leg
made him to look after chickens
then the eye that he took out from his father
he put it into his mother's eye
kangka duto vahle nate vanute vahmi lingcha
and he pour the magic water into it, and the eye opened
dothal kite vanu ruwng vachapa ruwng
then the mother and the son
lived very well, so it is said
